Take care of your Mala beads:- your personal mala beads are your sacred instrument and they are charged with energies and should be protected and looked after with great care and only handled by yourself.
They should not get wet or be slept in so as not to damage them and always kept in a safe place.

#malabeads #108 #108beads #prayerbeads #oneofakind #mala

The Guru bead/pendant on mala beads signifies the beginning and the end of your mantra/prayer.
Before you begin you hold guru and set your intentions for your prayer/mantra then begin going around touching each bead as you repeat your mantra/prayer.
Once the full cycle of 108 beads is complete and you want to continue you should flip the beads and go around again, you should not cross the guru bead as a sign of respect.
Start in your left hand and begin clockwise.

#malabeads #mala108 #108beads #mala #oneofakind #spiritualbeads #prayerbeads

Mala beads are used for meditation and prayer to help focus awareness and help retain concentration throughout while chanting your mantra or prayer.
It is a way of setting your intentions and cementing them to yourself and the universe as you touch each bead while repeating your mantra/prayer 108 times for a full cycle. 
108 is the ultimate number in numerology said to represent the sun, spiritual protection and destruction :- 1=Sun, 0=spiritual protection, 8=Saturn.  There are also 108 energy lines that connect to the heart as found in chakra practices and these lines lead of self realisation. 
108 is also seen as divine in astrology. The diameter of the sun is 108 times that of the earth, distance from earth to the moon is 108 times the moons diameter.
